<paragraph id="8BB6368C925C773EFF43F9A9FBC2BA90" blockId="12.[136,1452,1657,1936]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925C773EFF43F9A9FE2ABAD8" bold="true" box="[189,443,1657,1683]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925C773EFE45F9A9FD52BAD8" box="[443,707,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925C773EFE26F9A9FD52BAD8" box="[472,707,1657,1683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">Bertolonia cuspidata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B69925C773EFC7DF9A9FC61BADD" box="[899,1008,1657,1686]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.595" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" unit="km" value="3595.0">3,595 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B69925C773EFB64F9A9FB65BADD" box="[1178,1268,1657,1686]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.95" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" unit="km" value="595.0">595 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Endangered” (EN), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D925C773EFD69F94DFCA3BAFC" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[663,818,1693,1719]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been found only outside conservation units, mainly in the “Serra da Pedra Lascada” and “Serra do Corcovado”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136507925C773EFF43F935FC83BBC4" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C925C773EFF43F935FC83BBC4" blockId="12.[136,1452,1657,1936]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925C773EFF43F935FE98BAB4" bold="true" box="[189,265,1765,1791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925C773EFED8F935FD85BAB4" box="[294,532,1765,1791]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925C773EFED8F935FD85BAB4" box="[294,532,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Bertolonia cuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E925C773EFD3CF935FC97BAB4" box="[706,774,1765,1791]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation id="13322A09925C773EFB64F935FB7CBAB4" box="[1178,1261,1765,1791]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
), on shaded and moist slopes. Collected with flowers from July to February and fruits from August to March. The species can be recognized by the widely elliptic and glandulose-punctate leaf blades with a cuspidate apex, hypanthium glandulosepunctate and also glandulose-villose and petals with an apiculate apex ending in a glandular head. For more details see notes under 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925C773EFEEFF8A6FDEFBBC4" authority=", Bacci et al. (2018)" authorityName="Bacci" authorityYear="2018" box="[273,638,1909,1936]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925C773EFEEFF8A6FE0CBBC4" box="[273,413,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">B. cuspidata</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D925C773EFE55F8A5FDEFBBC4" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[427,638,1909,1936]" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925C773EFE0CF8A6FDB2BBC4" box="[498,547,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="165">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<tableCitation id="C68B0337925C773EFD46F8A5FC9DBBC4" box="[696,780,1909,1935]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="12" pageNumber="165" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
